description: Time series of the proportion of participants looking left over time for age group 'seven'. The blue line shows the proportion at each frame with 95% CI (gray area). The dotted red horizontal line indicates the calculated statistical threshold (0.38) for detecting a significant shift (baseline mean + 2.00*SD). The dashed purple line shows the baseline mean (0.23) during the baseline period (frames 0-5). The solid red vertical line marks the first significant shift frame (14). The green solid line indicates the First Body Frame at frame 3.

Time series showing the rate of change (derivative) of the looking-left proportion for age group 'seven'. The blue line indicates the frame-by-frame change in proportion. Peaks indicate rapid increases in looking left.
